    • Employee

      public Employee​(java.lang.Integer eid, java.lang.String firstName, java.lang.String lastName, java.lang.String position, java.lang.String email, java.lang.Integer teamId)
      A constructor for adding all information about the employee upon instantiation
      Parameters:
      eid - The Employee ID. Should be a unique non-negative integer value
      firstName - Employee's first name
      lastName - Employee's last name
      position - Employee's position within the company e.g. Associate
      email - The Employee's work email address
      teamId - The ID of the team in which the Employee is currently operating

    • Employee

      public Employee()
      A secondary constructor for when data for the Employee doesn't need to be entered upon instantiation. Individual data fields can be filled in individually using the other methods in this class
